-- Russian Linked to Club Fire Gets Jail Sentence, Rossiya-24 Says
-- B y   J a k e   R u d n i t s k y
-- 2012-05-14T07:57:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/russian-linked-to-club-fire-gets-jail-sentence-rossiya-24-says.html
Russian businessman Konstantin
Mrykhin was sentenced to six and a half years in prison for his
role in a fire at a Perm nightclub that killed 156 people in
2009, Rossiya-24 state television reported.  Mrykhin, a part-owner of the club, was extradited from
 Spain  after the fire; he was found guilty of failure to meet
safety standards, leading to the deaths of two or more people,
according to the report.  Link to original report:
{ http://www.vesti.ru/doc.html?id=793334 }  To contact the reporter on this story:
